    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Luca</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Iquique</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-03-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received March
                        25.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The delegation of the National Congress of Chile requests you, as an act of
                    neutrality, not to permit the shipments of silver belonging to the national
                    treasury of Chile on board of an American war vessel, as has been requested by
                    the dictator Balmaceda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Waldo Silva Barros Luca</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
